The paper discusses a methodology for mapping academic institutions based on their journal publication profiles, which involves the use of cluster analysis and dendrograms. This methodology can be applied to different disciplinary contexts, such as Information and Communication Technologies and Medicine and Pharmacology. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), which deals with the organization, management, and access to digital information. Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper touches upon topics related to network analysis, data mining, and privacy concerns in academic publishing.
